This paper deals with privacy threats in social networks and proposes a method to learn networks from random walk-based node similarities. The paper involves optimization problems and data mining techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, since the paper primarily focuses on social networks and privacy threats, cs.SI and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SD, cs.DS, and cs.LG.
